# Server-Side Patterns

## Configuration

- ALL constants go in `lib/config.js` (never hardcode URLs, thresholds, or paths)
- Environment variables override config defaults via `.env`
- File paths use `config.PATHS.*` relative to project root

## Error Handling

- Wrap ALL external API calls (Oref, Tzevaadom) in try/catch
- Return cached data on fetch failure (see `fetchFullHistory()` pattern)
- Log errors with context prefix: `[ML]`, `[API]`, `[Startup]`, `[retrain]`
- Never use empty catch blocks — at minimum log the error

## ML Model

- Model lives in `model/` directory, auto-reloaded via `fs.watch`
- Always validate model compatibility before loading (`validateModel()`)
- Prediction blending: `alpha * ML + (1-alpha) * distanceCurve`
- Alpha is capped at 0.70, computed during training based on accuracy + data volume
- Use `extractFeatures()` from `lib/ml/features.js` — never reimplement

## Module System

- Server code uses **CommonJS** (`require`/`module.exports`)
- Frontend code uses **ES modules** (`import`/`export`)
- These cannot cross-import — any shared logic must be duplicated with a comment explaining why

## Testing

```bash
npm test                  # Unit tests (Jest)
npm run check:features    # Verify feature alignment
npm run validate:model    # Check model compatibility
npm run test:calibration  # Model calibration validation
```
